    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A standardized chart of the chemical elements laid out in sequence by atomic number, arranged in horizontal rows and vertical columns, called periods and groups, so that elements with similar properties are in the same column.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047497/McGraw-Hill Dictionary of Scientific and Technical Terms [online] (2003)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047949/Merriam-Webster Dictionary [online] (2006-2008)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Una carta estandarizada de los elementos químicos dispuestas en secuencia según número atómico, ordenada en filas horizontales y columnas verticales, llamadas períodos y grupos, de manera que los elementos con propiedades similares se ubican en la misma columna.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Een gestandaardiseerde kaart met de chemische elementen, gerangschikt op atoomnummer en verdeeld in horizontale rijen en verticale kolommen, de zogeheten perioden en groepen, waardoor elementen met dezelfde eigenschappen in dezelfde kolom staan.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>化學元素的標準圖，按原子數的順序展開，依列（橫向）與欄（縱向）排列，稱為週期與族，具相似特性的元素位於同一欄。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Eine normierte Tabelle, in der die chemischen Elemente nach ihrer Atomzahl in horizontalen Reihen und vertikalen Spalten verzeichnet sind, die Perioden und Gruppen genannt werden, so dass Elemente mit ähnlichen Eigenschaften in derselben Spalte stehen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
